```python
start_mask = (df['is_decrease'])&(~df['is_decrease'].shift(1, fill_value=False))
end_mask = (df['is_decrease'])&(~df['is_decrease'].shift(-1, fill_value=False))
start_days = df.loc[start_mask,'day'].to_numpy()
end_days = df.loc[end_mask,'day'].to_numpy()
df_drop = pd.DataFrame({'start_day':start_days, 'end_day':end_days})
df_drop['length']=df_drop['end_day']-df_drop['start_day']+1
df_drop = df_drop[df_drop['length']>1]
display(df_drop)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7,4))
ax.plot(df['day'],df['value'], marker='o')
ax.set_title("Value Trend with Drop Periods")
ax.set_ylabel("Value")
ax.set_xlabel("Day")
ymin, ymax = ax.get_ylim()
day = df["day"].to_numpy()[:, None]                  # (N,1)
start = df_drop["start_day"].to_numpy()[None, :]     # (1,K)
end = df_drop["end_day"].to_numpy()[None, :]         # (1,K)

in_any_span = ((day >= start) & (day <= end)).any(axis=1)  # (N,)
ax.fill_between(
    df['day'], ymin, ymax,
    where=in_any_span,
    color="gray",
    alpha=0.3
)
ax.grid(True)
```
